Weiming,

Only the feature map features would be a problem and only the one from the XMLTypeDocumentRoot is significant problem because all dynamic demand created document roots extend that one base class.  That's why this problem has shown up only for this one case.  The map will generally not be populated by other classifiers from the same package but, at least in this case, by document roots from other packages, so limiting based on the size of the feature's type's package doesn't help, and keep in mind that the feature's type, getEType, is different  from the feature's containing class, getEContainingClass().

I'm not sure under which situations one ends up creating a feature map to which nothing is ever added, but that's the only situation I can imagine where the validator is created and then not used.  This seems orthogonal to the topic in question though, and certainly I wouldn't take the risk to change behavior for when the validator is created in a maintenance stream...


